{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:19:31Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","path":"/Users/ghost/core/nexus/tool/kick_dispatch.hexa","reason":"BUG#1 root-cause fix — _slugify() used string ordering ops (>=, <=) which return void on Linux hexa-lang runtime (ubu1/ubu2) but bool on Mac stage0. Rewrote to use index_of() — runtime-portable. Cross-host synced (ubu1, ubu2). Underlying hexa-lang runtime divergence remains hive blocker.","actor":"ghost","window_sec":120,"pid":56956,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 75 + raw 85","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"hexa_lang_runtime_divergence","fix_layer":"call-site portable rewrite","verification":"_slugify probe ubu1+ubu2 PASS; dry-run kick run_id correct on 3 hosts","upstream_blocker":"hive: file hexa-lang runtime divergence (string ordering ops void return on Linux)"}}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:29:10Z","op":"edit+sync","path":"/Users/ghost/core/hive/tool/subagent_dispatch.hexa","reason":"BUG#2 root-cause fix — _ai=2 hardcoded argv skip works on Mac stage0 (returns [binary,binary,...real_args]) but fails on Linux hexa_real (returns [binary,run,script.hexa,...real_args]) → cli[0]=script_path, parent_sid=script_path, child_sid=empty → mkfifo /tmp/subagent-relay-/path-.fifo path leak (D-2 incident). Replaced with cross-runtime skip-prefix loop: ends_with(/hexa,/hexa_real,/exe) + run + .hexa one-time. Synced ubu1+ubu2.","actor":"ghost","window_sec":300,"pid":83858,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 75 + raw 85","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"hexa_lang_args_runtime_divergence_class","fix_layer":"call-site portable rewrite","verification":"Mac local PASS (parent-A SID propagated); ubu1+ubu2 PASS (structured err message instead of mkfifo path leak)","class_bug_count":"25 _ai=2 instances across hive tools — only subagent_dispatch fixed (other tools may fail on remote invocation)"}}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:29:10Z","op":"edit+sync","path":"/Users/ghost/core/nexus/scripts/bin/hexa_remote","reason":"BUG#3 root-cause fix — Mac sets HEXA_LANG=/Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang globally so use self/stdlib/ai_err resolves; remote ssh shells inherit minimal env without HEXA_LANG → use directive fails to find stdlib → Runtime error: undefined function: ai_err_exit (D-2 incident). Inject HEXA_LANG via REMOTE_CMD with fallback chain $HOME/Dev/hexa-lang then $HOME/core/hexa-lang. PLUS rsynced hexa-lang/self/stdlib/ to ubu1+ubu2 (ubu1 had no stdlib subdirectory at all).","actor":"ghost","window_sec":300,"pid":83858,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 75 + raw 85","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"cross_host_stdlib_resolution","fix_layer":"hexa_remote env injection + stdlib rsync","verification":"ubu1+ubu2: subagent_dispatch parent-Z emits structured ai_err_exit message instead of Runtime error"}}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:29:56Z","op":"edit+sync","path":"/Users/ghost/core/hive/tool/subagent_dispatch.hexa","reason":"BUG#4 root-cause fix — `disown` bash-builtin used in nohup ... & disown pattern fails on POSIX sh / dash (Ubuntu sshd default shell). `nohup ... &` alone handles SIGHUP-immunity + background; `disown` was redundant. Removed both occurrences (lines 400, 407). Synced ubu1+ubu2.","actor":"ghost","window_sec":120,"pid":11341,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 75","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"shell_portability","fix_layer":"remove redundant bash-only builtin","verification":"diff confirms `disown` removed; nohup+& sufficient on POSIX sh"}}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:45:26Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","path":"/Users/ghost/core/nexus/scripts/bin/hexa_remote","reason":"BUG#5 root-cause fix — Mac ANTHROPIC_API_KEY env not propagated to remote ssh shell (cross-host credential resolution gap, BUG#3 와 동일 클래스). Inject via REMOTE_CMD env passthrough using printf 48715 for safe quoting. Empty Mac env → empty remote env → hive coding-agent emits raw 66 ai-native error (no degradation). Pre-flight warning for kick + claude_code argv pattern. Single-entry-point invariant: NO separate nexus_credential subcommand.","actor":"ghost","window_sec":120,"pid":0,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 75 + raw 85 + raw 66","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"cross_host_credential_resolution","fix_layer":"hexa_remote env passthrough + pre-flight ai-native warning"}}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T07:45:26Z","op":"edit+sync","path":"/Users/ghost/core/nexus/tool/kick_bench.hexa","reason":"BUG#6 root-cause fix — kick_bench did not forward --axes/--noise/--stratum to kick_dispatch → bench used kick_dispatch defaults (axes=design-strategy,falsifier-coverage = K=2) → raw 48 K>=3 orthogonality not exercised in benchmarks. Added 3 flag parsers + 3 forwarding lines.","actor":"ghost","window_sec":60,"pid":48715,"host":"Mac","prev_ts":"","sidecar_metadata_archived":{"raw_ref":"raw 1 + raw 48","level":1,"r4_session":"r4-2026-04-27","bug_class":"flag_propagation_gap","fix_layer":"forward 3 kick params"}}
{"ts": "2026-04-27T07:46:16Z", "op": "create+sync", "path": "/Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/self/stdlib/argv_skip.hexa", "reason": "BUG#2-class extension — extracted shared helper skip_invocation_prefix() from subagent_dispatch.hexa inline fix (lines 507-538). Mac stage0 args()=[bin,bin,...] needs skip=2; Linux hexa_real args()=[bin,run,script.hexa,...] needs skip=3. Helper handles both + edge cases (empty, already-stripped, bare exe). Refactored to nested-if (no &&) because Linux hexa runtime does NOT short-circuit && — `if i<len(raw) && raw[i]==…` crashes with index-out-of-bounds when raw is empty. Synced ubu1+ubu2.", "actor": "ghost", "window_sec": 0, "pid": 67509, "host": "Mac", "prev_ts": "", "sidecar_metadata_archived": {"raw_ref": "raw 1 + raw 75 + raw 85", "level": 1, "r4_session": "r4-2026-04-27", "bug_class": "hexa_lang_args_runtime_divergence_class", "fix_layer": "shared stdlib helper", "verification": "Mac+ubu1+ubu2: standalone helper test PASS (6 cases: mac_shape→2, linux_shape→3, stripped→0, empty→0, linux_norun→2, exe→1)", "depends_on": "BUG#2 (subagent_dispatch.hexa inline fix)", "discovery": "Linux && short-circuit divergence — `if i<len && raw[i]…` evaluates RHS even when LHS false, crashes on empty arrays"}}
