{"ts":"2026-04-27T19:09:00Z","op":"mac-resource-exhaustion-fix","path":"/Users/ghost/core/nexus/bin/hexa_rss_watchdog","raw_ref":"raw 75 + raw 93","actor":"claude-opus-4-7","window_sec":0,"host":"Mac","fix":"F1-watchdog-pattern-add-hexa_interp","summary":"Added hexa_interp.real to PATTERN regex (was hexa_stage0.real|hexa_v2|hexa_full only). Mac binary is hexa_interp.real — observed 2.87 GiB peak (PID 6333, raw_all --target-rule raw:99) and earlier 5.9 GiB peak (PID 67652). Without this rule the watchdog never fires for Mac-native interp loop. Default cap also lowered 4096 -> 3072 MiB (24 GiB Mac envelope)."}
